main event: On February 7, 1956, multiple witnesses in South Newton, Iowa, observed a bright, triangular-shaped object silently maneuvering in the sky.
interesting points: The object was described as brighter and larger than the stars in the sky.,The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes.,Witnesses reported that the object moved slowly to the east before disappearing.,There were multiple confirmed observers of the event.,The object was noted to be triangular in shape.
